    "abstractNote": "\"When Micheal the Syrian [...] wrote his famous chronicle, the Seldjuks had already settled in Asia Minor and founded their own political states. In this way the Christians living there entered into a narrower contact with this people. [...] Michael the Syrian devoted one chapter of his Chronicle to this issue. He is calling the Turks \"Turqaye\" or also \"Turkaye\". [...] Book 14 of his Chronicle is devoted to this people. [...] The informations offered by Michael on the Turks, are very different. We may subdivide them in two categories: the historical and the meta-historical informations.\" (pp. 39-40)",
